-- NII Won’t Get Brazil’s Approval to Buy Unicel, Veja Reports
-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 2012-11-24T19:29:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-24/nii-won-t-get-brazil-s-approval-to-buy-unicel-veja-reports.html
NII Holdings Inc. (NIHD) , which sells
wireless service under the Nextel brand name in Latin America,
won’t get approval from Brazil regulator Anatel to take over
Unicel do Brasil Telecomunicacoes Ltda, Veja magazine reported,
without saying where it got the information.  NII filed a request on Oct. 29 to buy Unicel, according to
a filling published on Anatel’s website.  The column item contained no comment from NII. Claudia Restrepo, an NII spokeswoman, didn’t respond to a telephone call
and an e-mail today from Bloomberg News outside of regular
business hours.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ney Hayashi in Sao Paulo at 
 ncruz4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in  New York  at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  